<TITLE> ERD's Bhuiyan gets top ADB job </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 19 (bdnews24.com)Aminul Islam Bhuiyan, the ERD secretary who has been made an OSD at establishment ministry, will be the new Alternate Executive Director from Bangladesh at the Asian Development Bank, officials said. The government announced his transfer from the economic relations division Sunday but did not name his successor. Bhuiyan told bdnews24.com that he would replace a Bhutanese official for the Manila-based job. "Pending completion of my lien formalities, I am hoping to take up the new assignment on Nov 1," the secretary said. Several other senior civil servants were transferred Sunday. M Rafiquzzaman, now a joint secretary at establishment, will be chief executive officer for Bangladesh Better Business Forum. 
